<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER RT-610 SERIES - REMOVE - LEFT REVERSE IDLER GEAR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="4">
        <title>LEFT REVERSE IDLER GEAR</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a curved pry bar to walk bearing from the idler bore in the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302436">Figure 36</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302436" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302436" filename="../figg13/G1302436.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 36. Use Pry Bar to Walk Bearing From Idler Bore</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear idler washer and holder from the bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302437">Figure 37</hotlnk>). If necessary, bend holder lugs and remove the washer from
                the holder.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302437" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302437" filename="../figg13/G1302437.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 37. Remove Rear Idler Washer and Holder From Bore</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse idler gear from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302438">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302438" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302438" filename="../figg13/G1302438.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 38. Remove Reverse Idler Gear From Case</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the idler bearing from the reverse idler gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302439">Figure 39</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302439" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302439" filename="../figg13/G1302439.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 39. Remove Idler Bearing From Reverse Idler Gear</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the front idler washer from the case.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
